article.headline: Troy State 68, Stetson 66
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Rob Lewin scored 20 points and had 14 rebounds to lead Troy State to a 68-66 comeback victory over Stetson on Sunday. The win gave Troy State (22-5, 18-2 Atlantic Sun Conference) the regular-season league title and extended its NCAA Division I school record winning streak to 11 games. Stetson led throughout much of the game, including a 64-58 margin with 4:03 to play. But Troy State went on a 10-point run anchored by back-to-back buckets by Jerome Stamper and a 3-pointer from the corner by Kendrick Johnson. Stamper's score at 1:42 put the Trojans ahead 65-64 and Johnson's 3-pointer made it 68-64 with 58 seconds left. Stetson (12-14, 10-10) was led by E.J. Gordon, who had 18 points. But it was Gordon who lost possession of the ball as Stetson had a chance to tie or win the game with four seconds left. Anthony Register chipped in 14 points and senior guard Derek DeWitt added 13 for the Hatters. Lewin was 7-of-11 from the floor on a day when the second-highest scoring team in Division I had trouble making shots. The Trojans hit just 41.9 percent (26 of 62) of their field-goal attempts. Stamper and Johnson each added 14 points for Troy State.
